Cygwin- a layer that allows Unix-like commands to run on Windows.
ssh command- securely connects to a remote server or system over a network using the Secure Shell (SSH) protocol. It is widely used for remote administration, file transfers, 
and running applications on remote machines.
bash- a command-line interpreter and a scripting language. used on Unix-like operating systems such as Linux and macOS. It allows users to interact with the operating system
by entering commands into a terminal. 

We have to log into the game. The host is on port 2220.

How to log:
ssh username@hostname -p port_number

 SSH usually runs on port 22; otherwise, we have to use the -p option
